<doc>Scan the running application's UI tree and generate a locators.yaml file.

Walks the live Windows UIA accessibility tree, scores every element for
locator quality, and writes a ready-to-use &lt;span class="name"&gt;`locators.yaml&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="name"&gt; to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="name"&gt;output_path&lt;/span&gt;`.
Drop the output file into &lt;span class="name"&gt;`screens/&lt;screen&gt;/locators.yaml&lt;/span&gt;`, review the
generated keys, and it is ready to use.

Score key:
| ★★★ | automation_id — developer-set, most stable        |
| ★★  | name — accessible label or button caption          |
| ★   | class_name — Win32 class, stable but less unique   |

Examples:
| Scan Application Screen |
| Scan Application Screen | output_path=screens/login/locators.yaml |
| Scan Application Screen | output_path=screens/dashboard/locators.yaml | max_depth=5 |</doc>
<shortdoc>Scan the running application's UI tree and generate a locators.yaml file.</shortdoc>
</kw>
